  "response": "Here are some excellent books to learn Mechatronics and Robotics from a fundamental level:\n\nMechatronics Fundamentals:\n1. \"Mechatronics: Principles and Applications\" by Godfrey Uzochukwu Bolton\n2. \"Introduction to Mechatronics and Measurement Systems\" by David Alciatore\n3. \"Mechatronics: Electronic Control Systems in Mechanical and Electrical Engineering\" by W. Bolton\n\nRobotics Fundamentals:\n1. \"Introduction to Robotics: Mechanics and Control\" by John J. Craig\n2. \"Probabilistic Robotics\" by Sebastian Thrun, Wolfram Burgard, and Dieter Fox\n3. \"Modern Robotics: Mechanics, Planning, and Control\" by Kevin Lynch and Frank Park\n\nComprehensive Books:\n1. \"Springer Handbook of Robotics\" - Comprehensive reference\n2. \"Robotics, Vision and Control\" by Peter Corke\n\nProgramming and Technical Skills:\n1. \"Robot Building for Beginners\" by David Cook\n2. \"Learning ROS for Robotics Programming\" by Enrique Fern\u00e1ndez\n\nBeginner-Friendly:\n1. \"Make: Electronics\" by Charles Platt\n2. \"Arduino Robotics\" by John-David Warren\n\nAdvanced Theoretical:\n1. \"Rigid Body Dynamics Algorithms\" by Roy Featherstone\n2. \"Planning Algorithms\" by Steven LaValle\n\nThese books cover various aspects from basic concepts to advanced techniques.",
